entries.meaning: A standstill resulting from the opposition of two evenly matched forces; a stalemate or impasse.
examples: The negotiation ended in deadlock, with neither party willing to compromise on the price.

entries.meaning: (computing) An inability to continue due to two programs or devices each requiring a response from the other before completing an operation.

verbs.description: deadlock (third-person singular simple present deadlocks, present participle deadlocking, simple past and past participle deadlocked)

entries.meaning: (intransitive) To cause or come to a deadlock.
